com.ing.software.common

Class Lazy<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ing.software.common.Lazy<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - object

    public class Lazy<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Lazily instantiate an object. Useful if in a collection of objects, only some fields of some elements are accessed. Please mind that everything before :: operator is executed in place. Ex: instead of (...::toList) use (() -> ... .toList()).
